      public int getMaxSizeOfExecutorsArray()
      Returns maximum size of array returned by getWorkQueueExecutorInfoArray(gw.api.web.tools.WorkQueueDisplayInfo) method. However note that if the number of active executors exceeds this value, all active executors will be listed anyway.
      Returns:
      maximum size of array returned by getWorkQueueExecutorInfoArray(gw.api.web.tools.WorkQueueDisplayInfo) method

    • getMaxSizeOfWorkerRunsArray

    • getWorkQueueExecutorInfoArray

      public WorkQueueExecutorDisplayInfo[] getWorkQueueExecutorInfoArray(WorkQueueDisplayInfo queue)
      Returns array of beans which contain basic information about active and terminated executors.

      Note the maximum size of the array is max value out of MAX_EXECUTORS and number of active executors. Therefore at least all active executors will be listed. If the number of active executors is less than MAX_EXECUTORS, then the returned array will contain latest terminated executors.

      Parameters:
      queue - queue
      Returns:
      array of beans contains basic executors info
